						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīrarājēndradēva. Year 13: A.D. 1219.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Registers that the <hi rend="italic">kāṇi</hi> rights in the temples of Tirumunnaiyāḷuḍaiyār and Srī Bhūtaṉ Munnamuraippāṉ were sold for money by two <hi rend="italic">śiva-brāhmaṇas</hi>, Tiruvēgampamuḍaiyān Piḷḷaiyāḻvi and Piḷḷaiyāḻvi Tiruvēgampamuḍaiyāṉ of <hi rend="italic">Kāsu-gōtram</hi> from Teṉkarai Koḍuvēli in Vaḍaparisāra-nāḍu.</p>						

